spans.text: The light he lends to you
wakes the genial birth , Drops fatness on the pregnant earth , And crowns the laughing field
fatness on the pregnant earth , And crowns the laughing field
sweep The ruffled surface of the deep , With us confess your God ;
whose never-varying light , Absent , adds horror to the night , But present
close array , Surround his awful shrine
the spring , With annual verdure bloom
that ambitious rise , And heave your summits to the skies , Revere his awful nod
the Ruler of the skies , Whose hand the genial sap supplies
Praise him , at whose almighty nod The rugged rock dissolving flowed , And formed a springing well
the spacious earth surround , And roll from shore to shore
whose heavenly aid You languish , faint
You slaves of the laborious plough , Your stubborn necks submissive bow , And bend your wearied knees
your songs his praise display , Till heaven itself shall melt away
his praise display , Till heaven itself shall melt away
